1
00:00:19,740 --> 00:00:23,240
♪Hey, you, you, you,
why is it you again?♪

2
00:00:23,540 --> 00:00:27,570
♪Always stumbling upon
my little secrets♪

3
00:00:27,970 --> 00:00:31,990
♪Falling on my brows, my lashes,
even the strands by my mouth♪

4
00:00:31,990 --> 00:00:36,660
♪Like my favorite kitten
on a rainy spring afternoon♪

5
00:00:36,660 --> 00:00:41,320
♪Hey, you, you, you,
why is it you again?♪

6
00:00:41,320 --> 00:00:45,110
♪You effortlessly awaken
my protective instincts♪

7
00:00:45,390 --> 00:00:49,450
♪Hitting all my little thoughts,
my doubts, and my temper♪

8
00:00:49,730 --> 00:00:54,300
♪Like my favorite beer and fried chicken
in autumn, or spicy boiled fish in winter♪

9
00:00:54,600 --> 00:00:58,770
♪Why is it you again?
That sweet way you speak♪

10
00:00:59,000 --> 00:01:03,080
♪As if the whole world knows
my mind is full of you♪

11
00:01:03,360 --> 00:01:07,530
♪Why is it still you?
That secret smile behind your cool facade♪

12
00:01:07,730 --> 00:01:11,760
♪I might as well play along.
Let me protect you♪

13
00:01:12,060 --> 00:01:16,190
♪Why is it always you?
The smile at the corner of your lips♪

14
00:01:16,480 --> 00:01:20,590
♪Before I knew it, the words blurted out,
"I like you. I only like you."♪

15
00:01:29,530 --> 00:01:33,220
♪Before I knew it, the words blurted out,
"I like you. I only like you."♪

16
00:01:33,220 --> 00:01:34,040
=Love Has Fireworks=

17
00:01:34,040 --> 00:01:34,861
(Based on "Investment Men and Women"
by Hong Er on Jinjiang Literature City)

18
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:37,980
=Episode 9=

19
00:01:40,150 --> 00:01:40,710
Hello?

20
00:01:41,070 --> 00:01:42,790
Gosh, you were sleeping?

21
00:01:42,920 --> 00:01:43,680
I just woke up.

22
00:01:44,040 --> 00:01:45,790
Gosh, you were sleeping?

23
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:47,590
HR couldn't reach you,

24
00:01:47,680 --> 00:01:48,640
so they called me.

25
00:01:49,350 --> 00:01:49,590
HR?

26
00:01:50,150 --> 00:01:51,870
HR called me?

27
00:01:52,480 --> 00:01:53,560
What for?

28
00:01:54,230 --> 00:01:56,120
What else could it be? Good news.

29
00:01:56,280 --> 00:01:57,870
Congratulations. Your dream came true.

30
00:01:57,870 --> 00:01:58,560
Get over here.

31
00:01:59,590 --> 00:02:01,790
You mean I got reinstated?

32
00:02:01,920 --> 00:02:02,760
Seriously?

33
00:02:03,040 --> 00:02:03,590
You know what?

34
00:02:03,590 --> 00:02:05,230
I just dreamed that I got my job back.

35
00:02:05,560 --> 00:02:06,310
Cut the chatter.

36
00:02:06,350 --> 00:02:07,755
(Hejing Securities)
Get over here.

37
00:02:09,310 --> 00:02:09,960
No.

38
00:02:09,960 --> 00:02:12,600
I can't get my hopes up
for nothing again like last time.

39
00:02:12,644 --> 00:02:14,120
I need to hear it from Ms. Fang

40
00:02:14,120 --> 00:02:15,680
before I believe it.

41
00:02:17,000 --> 00:02:17,630
I'm on my way.

42
00:02:30,240 --> 00:02:31,910
You know why I asked you here,
don't you?

43
00:02:34,311 --> 00:02:35,720
Why are you looking at me like that?

44
00:02:37,430 --> 00:02:39,490
I'll only believe it
if I hear it from you.

45
00:02:39,500 --> 00:02:41,780
Anything anyone else says,
I take with a grain of salt.

46
00:02:42,740 --> 00:02:44,060
Your report was valuable.

47
00:02:44,460 --> 00:02:46,700
Even financial tricks
on Shanlifang's level

48
00:02:46,700 --> 00:02:47,740
were uncovered by you.

49
00:02:49,740 --> 00:02:51,860
I only found the original data

50
00:02:52,060 --> 00:02:53,220
and confirmed it.

51
00:02:53,380 --> 00:02:54,580
Without hard evidence,

52
00:02:54,700 --> 00:02:56,500
all suspicions are just speculation.

53
00:02:56,700 --> 00:02:58,622
And you were the one
who found the evidence.

54
00:02:58,800 --> 00:03:00,700
You proved your ability
through your actions.

55
00:03:01,060 --> 00:03:04,300
So, welcome back to Hejing to assist me.

56
00:03:06,288 --> 00:03:07,266
Please have a seat.

57
00:03:08,380 --> 00:03:09,180
That's wonderful.

58
00:03:09,900 --> 00:03:12,660
Thank you for giving me a second chance,
Ms. Fang.

59
00:03:12,820 --> 00:03:14,180
I'll give it everything I've got.

60
00:03:14,300 --> 00:03:16,500
I'll straighten out all
of Shanlifang's accounts and...

61
00:03:16,500 --> 00:03:18,540
Don't get too fired up just yet.

62
00:03:18,820 --> 00:03:19,780
You're still new here.

63
00:03:20,500 --> 00:03:22,260
You need to observe more and learn more.

64
00:03:24,622 --> 00:03:25,990
Don't think too highly of yourself.

65
00:03:26,260 --> 00:03:28,220
Pride comes before a fall.

66
00:03:28,620 --> 00:03:30,100
Alright. I'll keep that in mind.

67
00:03:30,700 --> 00:03:33,300
Also, we've signed
an agreement with Zhizhong

68
00:03:33,300 --> 00:03:35,020
regarding the division
of responsibilities.

69
00:03:35,020 --> 00:03:35,911
Zhizhong will be the one

70
00:03:35,920 --> 00:03:37,730
to formally raise
Shanlifang's financial issues.

71
00:03:37,740 --> 00:03:40,066
So don't say a word about this
to anyone outside. Understood?

72
00:03:40,300 --> 00:03:40,820
Understood.

73
00:03:41,180 --> 00:03:42,660
I'll focus on doing my job well.

74
00:03:43,140 --> 00:03:43,540
Very good.

75
00:03:43,700 --> 00:03:44,700
Oh, right, Ms. Fang.

76
00:03:45,577 --> 00:03:46,540
What will I be doing

77
00:03:47,020 --> 00:03:49,220
after joining the team?

78
00:03:49,300 --> 00:03:50,540
I'd like to prepare in advance.

79
00:03:52,700 --> 00:03:53,380
Running errands.

80
00:03:57,180 --> 00:03:58,780
Okay. Thank you, Ms. Fang.

81
00:04:01,500 --> 00:04:03,660
You'll put this information
into the spreadsheet...

82
00:04:04,300 --> 00:04:05,100
Look.

83
00:04:05,300 --> 00:04:07,740
Moli, Zhaozhao, Zijun.

84
00:04:07,980 --> 00:04:09,020
I'm back.

85
00:04:10,020 --> 00:04:11,940
We heard about it.
We missed you so much.

86
00:04:11,940 --> 00:04:13,300
I missed you guys, too.

87
00:04:13,300 --> 00:04:15,500
Seeing you come back,
we're genuinely happy for you.

88
00:04:15,500 --> 00:04:17,700
It proves that as long as
you're willing to work hard,

89
00:04:17,711 --> 00:04:19,860
the company won't fire
a capable person for no reason.

90
00:04:20,020 --> 00:04:20,580
Well said.

91
00:04:20,940 --> 00:04:22,660
Hard work never lets effort go to waste.

92
00:04:23,444 --> 00:04:26,220
Congratulations. Got assigned straight
to the front-office project team.

93
00:04:26,220 --> 00:04:28,220
The core department
of investment banking.

94
00:04:28,420 --> 00:04:29,700
But Ms. Fang told me

95
00:04:29,700 --> 00:04:31,360
that I'm starting out running errands.

96
00:04:31,380 --> 00:04:33,820
Still, you'll have unlimited potential,

97
00:04:33,940 --> 00:04:34,740
right?

98
00:04:34,820 --> 00:04:35,300
Qian Fei.

99
00:04:45,940 --> 00:04:46,860
You must be thrilled.

100
00:04:46,888 --> 00:04:48,860
I got transferred,
and you filled in my place.

101
00:04:49,100 --> 00:04:50,180
What are you on about?

102
00:04:50,700 --> 00:04:51,740
Stop pretending.

103
00:04:51,940 --> 00:04:53,340
Isn't this all thanks to you?

104
00:04:54,220 --> 00:04:56,340
If you hadn't snitched to Ms. Fang,

105
00:04:56,700 --> 00:04:57,940
would I have gotten reassigned?

106
00:04:58,860 --> 00:05:00,220
Everyone, be careful around her.

107
00:05:00,900 --> 00:05:03,340
To get her job back, she'll do anything

108
00:05:03,580 --> 00:05:05,100
to take someone else's position.

109
00:05:06,140 --> 00:05:07,380
I'm living proof.

110
00:05:08,300 --> 00:05:10,060
What's that got to do with me?

111
00:05:12,420 --> 00:05:14,220
Fei, when are you officially starting?

112
00:05:14,333 --> 00:05:15,660
Probably in the next few days.

113
00:05:25,580 --> 00:05:26,620
I'm back.

114
00:05:37,260 --> 00:05:39,060
(The landlady's mood seems off.)

115
00:05:39,700 --> 00:05:40,980
(Did Fang Yun play me?)

116
00:05:41,380 --> 00:05:43,460
(Was she never planning to let her
return to Hejing?)

117
00:05:43,660 --> 00:05:44,780
You're cleaning again?

118
00:05:45,060 --> 00:05:46,940
The place looks spotless.

119
00:05:51,980 --> 00:05:52,780
Honestly,

120
00:05:53,666 --> 00:05:55,266
if you put all this energy into chores,

121
00:05:55,290 --> 00:05:57,420
how are you supposed
to have any left for work?

122
00:05:57,500 --> 00:05:59,244
Why don't you hire a cleaning service?

123
00:05:59,700 --> 00:06:01,300
Housework helps me relax.

124
00:06:02,700 --> 00:06:03,900
You have a hobby like that?

125
00:06:05,220 --> 00:06:05,900
Foot.

126
00:06:12,500 --> 00:06:13,860
By the way, I got reinstated.

127
00:06:14,380 --> 00:06:16,220
Ms. Fang assigned me to Shanlifang.

128
00:06:16,580 --> 00:06:17,180
Really?

129
00:06:17,580 --> 00:06:20,740
That's great. Very good.

130
00:06:22,140 --> 00:06:23,100
Why are you so excited?

131
00:06:24,380 --> 00:06:24,820
I...

132
00:06:25,740 --> 00:06:27,580
You got your job back.

133
00:06:27,700 --> 00:06:29,660
Doesn't that mean
I get extra dishes now?

134
00:06:29,700 --> 00:06:30,340
I'm happy.

135
00:06:31,733 --> 00:06:32,800
But something's off.

136
00:06:32,820 --> 00:06:35,400
This isn't what I imagined you'd be like
after getting reinstated.

137
00:06:35,422 --> 00:06:36,888
Why don't you seem excited at all?

138
00:06:38,380 --> 00:06:40,100
Where's that fearless determination
you had

139
00:06:40,100 --> 00:06:41,940
when you were set on joining

140
00:06:42,020 --> 00:06:42,700
Fang Yun's team?

141
00:06:42,780 --> 00:06:44,140
Bring it back.

142
00:06:44,260 --> 00:06:46,140
Celebrate. Perk up.

143
00:06:46,533 --> 00:06:48,111
I have something to ask you.

144
00:06:50,700 --> 00:06:51,340
What is it?

145
00:06:52,700 --> 00:06:55,500
Ms. Fang said
we have to keep this confidential.

146
00:06:55,780 --> 00:06:58,100
You alone would negotiate
with Shanlifang.

147
00:07:00,140 --> 00:07:02,140
Why are you talking
all of this on by yourself?

148
00:07:03,580 --> 00:07:04,340
Why else?

149
00:07:04,620 --> 00:07:06,860
Because I'm capable.
I like being in the spotlight.

150
00:07:07,100 --> 00:07:08,220
Aren't you worried

151
00:07:08,220 --> 00:07:09,780
you might completely offend Shanlifang?

152
00:07:12,500 --> 00:07:13,380
I know.

153
00:07:16,500 --> 00:07:17,500
What am I afraid of?

154
00:07:18,533 --> 00:07:21,200
If you want to accomplish big things,
don't sweat the small stuff.

155
00:07:21,220 --> 00:07:22,644
I don't care about things like that.

156
00:07:22,820 --> 00:07:23,740
I really don't get

157
00:07:23,740 --> 00:07:24,940
how someone like you

158
00:07:24,940 --> 00:07:25,980
became the project leader.

159
00:07:35,577 --> 00:07:36,660
What are you looking at?

160
00:07:39,780 --> 00:07:40,980
Nothing. Nothing at all.

161
00:07:43,777 --> 00:07:45,180
I still have another question.

162
00:07:46,860 --> 00:07:47,460
Another one?

163
00:07:52,300 --> 00:07:53,580
Well, one...

164
00:07:54,580 --> 00:07:56,180
One question for one meal.

165
00:07:59,020 --> 00:08:01,380
I can cook for you. Do you dare eat it?

166
00:08:01,860 --> 00:08:03,220
What do you mean?

167
00:08:04,220 --> 00:08:06,300
Yes, you've got guts.
But you've got no shame.

168
00:08:07,260 --> 00:08:07,940
What do you mean?

169
00:08:13,111 --> 00:08:14,540
(Li Yifei: Authentic
Da Hong Pao Tea Egg)

170
00:08:14,540 --> 00:08:14,900
Uh.

171
00:08:15,380 --> 00:08:16,540
Didn't I hide it from you?

172
00:08:16,660 --> 00:08:17,380
How come?

173
00:08:17,511 --> 00:08:19,780
It's my first time doing this.
I'm still figuring it out.

174
00:08:21,020 --> 00:08:23,060
I suddenly feel uncomfortable.

175
00:08:23,133 --> 00:08:24,500
My back hurts. My waist hurts.

176
00:08:25,940 --> 00:08:26,780
Argh.

177
00:08:36,020 --> 00:08:37,780
My dinner is gone.

178
00:08:42,700 --> 00:08:44,740
(I even saved room for it.)

179
00:08:44,740 --> 00:08:46,660
(I thought she would make dinner
to thank me.)

180
00:08:47,220 --> 00:08:49,260
(I thought a feast was waiting for me.)

181
00:08:49,940 --> 00:08:51,380
(Poor me.)

182
00:08:51,980 --> 00:08:52,940
I'm not happy!

183
00:09:26,500 --> 00:09:28,020
I made too much for dinner.

184
00:09:28,740 --> 00:09:30,460
Rather than dump it in the trash,

185
00:09:30,500 --> 00:09:32,580
I might as well feed some animal.

186
00:09:33,180 --> 00:09:34,700
If you want to eat, come over.

187
00:09:53,460 --> 00:09:54,700
Hurry up.

188
00:09:57,340 --> 00:09:58,100
Look at you.

189
00:09:58,980 --> 00:10:00,380
I never said I wanted to eat.

190
00:10:02,220 --> 00:10:03,140
Fine, fine.

191
00:10:08,580 --> 00:10:10,580
What? Not using serving spoons?

192
00:10:10,688 --> 00:10:12,177
I thought you hated sharing food.

193
00:10:12,222 --> 00:10:13,260
I'm afraid you'll poison me.

194
00:10:13,460 --> 00:10:14,820
Eating from the same plate is safer.

195
00:10:15,780 --> 00:10:17,780
How did I end up with
such an annoying tenant?

196
00:10:18,511 --> 00:10:20,380
How did I end up with
such a generous landlady

197
00:10:20,380 --> 00:10:21,940
who also happens to cook so well?

198
00:10:22,300 --> 00:10:23,380
You're just buttering me up.

199
00:10:23,940 --> 00:10:25,380
Do you want something from me?

200
00:10:26,500 --> 00:10:27,660
What could I possibly want?

201
00:10:27,844 --> 00:10:29,133
I have no ulterior motive.

202
00:10:30,100 --> 00:10:30,700
Eat up.

203
00:10:36,140 --> 00:10:36,700
Who is it?

204
00:10:38,620 --> 00:10:39,500
Who's there?

205
00:10:44,180 --> 00:10:45,460
- Hello. Is Mr. Li home?
- Hello.

206
00:10:48,577 --> 00:10:50,540
Li Yifei, what big piece
did you buy this time?

207
00:10:50,820 --> 00:10:51,580
It's mine.

208
00:10:52,540 --> 00:10:53,500
Great. It's arrived.

209
00:10:53,780 --> 00:10:54,380
Come on in.

210
00:10:54,822 --> 00:10:56,550
Take it apart first
or assemble it first?

211
00:10:56,580 --> 00:10:58,266
- Take it apart first.
- Okay. This way.

212
00:10:59,222 --> 00:11:00,060
What are you doing?

213
00:11:01,422 --> 00:11:02,580
We're taking all of this apart?

214
00:11:02,580 --> 00:11:03,300
All of it.

215
00:11:03,300 --> 00:11:04,580
Just throw them away.

216
00:11:04,740 --> 00:11:05,260
Sure.

217
00:11:06,733 --> 00:11:07,820
Li Yifei, get out here.

218
00:11:08,220 --> 00:11:08,740
I'm busy.

219
00:11:08,822 --> 00:11:09,555
Get out here.

220
00:11:14,900 --> 00:11:16,260
Careful.

221
00:11:16,666 --> 00:11:17,755
Don't bump into anything.

222
00:11:19,900 --> 00:11:20,420
What's wrong?

223
00:11:20,420 --> 00:11:22,111
Did I ever agree
to let you change the bed?

224
00:11:22,860 --> 00:11:23,580
You did.

225
00:11:24,100 --> 00:11:24,940
When?

226
00:11:25,460 --> 00:11:26,700
There was this one time

227
00:11:26,900 --> 00:11:27,780
when you were drunk.

228
00:11:28,110 --> 00:11:30,540
You had only started drinking,
so you weren't completely wasted.

229
00:11:30,555 --> 00:11:31,622
You just don't remember.

230
00:11:32,660 --> 00:11:33,340
Did I?

231
00:11:34,860 --> 00:11:35,780
Yeah. You forgot.

232
00:11:36,820 --> 00:11:37,420
Well...

233
00:11:38,540 --> 00:11:41,140
If I agreed,
then go ahead and change it.

234
00:11:42,060 --> 00:11:43,700
But somehow, I don't quite believe you.

235
00:11:48,180 --> 00:11:50,860
Would I lie to you
over something this trivial?

236
00:11:51,580 --> 00:11:52,940
That day, you told me

237
00:11:52,940 --> 00:11:55,900
you'd originally planned to turn
the bed in my room

238
00:11:55,900 --> 00:11:57,266
into a mother-and-child bed

239
00:11:57,333 --> 00:11:58,740
after you got married and had kids.

240
00:11:59,540 --> 00:12:01,380
But then, you weren't
getting married anymore.

241
00:12:01,466 --> 00:12:03,266
Right? And there
wouldn't be any kids either.

242
00:12:03,311 --> 00:12:05,244
You said just looking at that bed
upset you.

243
00:12:05,355 --> 00:12:07,460
So I figured I'd help you replace it.

244
00:12:07,460 --> 00:12:08,620
Free of charge.

245
00:12:09,020 --> 00:12:10,780
Out of sight, out of mind.

246
00:12:11,140 --> 00:12:12,340
And you agreed.

247
00:12:12,460 --> 00:12:13,700
You even thanked me.

248
00:12:13,822 --> 00:12:15,440
And now you've forgotten all about it.

249
00:12:15,500 --> 00:12:16,740
Careful.

250
00:12:16,980 --> 00:12:17,500
Alright then.

251
00:12:17,888 --> 00:12:18,900
Go ahead and install it.

252
00:12:19,180 --> 00:12:20,540
Keep the noise down. It's late.

253
00:12:20,700 --> 00:12:21,060
Okay.

254
00:12:22,380 --> 00:12:23,780
Sir, we'll keep it down.

255
00:12:24,700 --> 00:12:25,100
Okay.

256
00:12:37,260 --> 00:12:39,700
♪Zhen fell in love with Qiang♪

257
00:12:40,300 --> 00:12:44,180
♪On a starry night♪

258
00:12:46,340 --> 00:12:47,540
This is amazing.

259
00:12:48,300 --> 00:12:51,300
I can finally roll around in bed.

260
00:12:55,300 --> 00:12:57,700
This is so comfortable.

261
00:12:58,300 --> 00:12:59,700
You scared me.

262
00:13:01,340 --> 00:13:02,420
I thought it over carefully.

263
00:13:02,555 --> 00:13:04,540
I definitely never agreed
to let you change the bed

264
00:13:04,555 --> 00:13:05,777
while I was drunk.

265
00:13:08,580 --> 00:13:09,300
You did.

266
00:13:12,871 --> 00:13:14,740
I know myself.

267
00:13:14,940 --> 00:13:16,740
I'm extremely careful with money.

268
00:13:17,300 --> 00:13:18,620
If I'd agreed,

269
00:13:18,733 --> 00:13:20,180
I definitely would've talked to you

270
00:13:20,244 --> 00:13:21,980
about depreciation on the old furniture.

271
00:13:22,180 --> 00:13:23,460
But obviously, I didn't.

272
00:13:26,660 --> 00:13:27,820
That's a good point.

273
00:13:28,060 --> 00:13:29,250
I've seen right through you.

274
00:13:29,260 --> 00:13:30,420
Don't be mad.

275
00:13:30,420 --> 00:13:32,020
This bed is really comfortable. Try it.

276
00:13:33,500 --> 00:13:34,500
Landlady! Qian Fei!

277
00:13:34,820 --> 00:13:36,620
Don't be mad. Come on.

278
00:13:36,620 --> 00:13:40,260
(Shanghai World Financial Center)

279
00:13:45,820 --> 00:13:46,540
Dang Yu.

280
00:13:58,777 --> 00:13:59,900
What are you doing here?

281
00:14:00,400 --> 00:14:02,711
Last time, you said to contact me
when you were free,

282
00:14:02,860 --> 00:14:04,660
but you never gave me your contact.

283
00:14:04,660 --> 00:14:06,488
So I could only come here
and wait for you.

284
00:14:07,100 --> 00:14:08,060
I forgot.

285
00:14:08,740 --> 00:14:09,580
What's it?

286
00:14:10,900 --> 00:14:12,900
Didn't we agree
that I'd treat you to a meal?

287
00:14:12,900 --> 00:14:14,580
We'd invite Qian Fei and Li Yifei too.

288
00:14:17,380 --> 00:14:19,420
I think there was something like that.

289
00:14:20,060 --> 00:14:21,340
So I wanted to ask if

290
00:14:21,460 --> 00:14:23,500
you're free tomorrow night
to grab a meal together.

291
00:14:24,980 --> 00:14:27,380
I've got a side job tomorrow night.

292
00:14:28,500 --> 00:14:30,220
What about lunchtime?

293
00:14:31,060 --> 00:14:32,860
I'm busy at noon, too.

294
00:14:33,420 --> 00:14:34,740
Let's do it another day.

295
00:14:34,780 --> 00:14:35,300
No.

296
00:14:35,700 --> 00:14:36,940
I want to lock in

297
00:14:36,940 --> 00:14:37,660
a time today.

298
00:14:39,060 --> 00:14:39,780
Why?

299
00:14:42,580 --> 00:14:43,540
Because

300
00:14:45,155 --> 00:14:47,500
the last time at Qian Fei's place,
I kind of scared her.

301
00:14:47,644 --> 00:14:49,000
I want to take her out for a meal,

302
00:14:49,088 --> 00:14:50,777
but I don't think it's appropriate

303
00:14:50,800 --> 00:14:51,900
to ask her out one-on-one.

304
00:14:52,060 --> 00:14:54,500
So I was hoping you and Li Yifei
could come along.

305
00:15:06,066 --> 00:15:07,420
That sounds pretty reasonable.

306
00:15:09,444 --> 00:15:11,500
I knew it. You insisted on
making it a group dinner,

307
00:15:11,500 --> 00:15:12,740
and it had to be four people.

308
00:15:13,500 --> 00:15:14,940
You wanted to ask Qian Fei out,

309
00:15:14,940 --> 00:15:16,800
but you were too shy to say so,
didn't you?

310
00:15:16,888 --> 00:15:18,020
Actually, it's not...

311
00:15:18,020 --> 00:15:18,780
It's fine.

312
00:15:19,420 --> 00:15:20,940
Let's do tomorrow at noon.

313
00:15:21,140 --> 00:15:22,620
I'll move some things around,

314
00:15:22,820 --> 00:15:24,460
and Qian Fei should be free too.

315
00:15:25,740 --> 00:15:26,500
It's settled then.

316
00:15:27,180 --> 00:15:27,820
Alright.

317
00:15:29,911 --> 00:15:31,220
Let's add each other on WeChat.

318
00:15:41,540 --> 00:15:42,060
Done.

319
00:15:44,020 --> 00:15:44,540
I'm off.

320
00:15:44,977 --> 00:15:45,820
See you tomorrow.

321
00:15:46,260 --> 00:15:46,980
See you tomorrow.

322
00:16:02,540 --> 00:16:03,980
Hello, dear.

323
00:16:04,380 --> 00:16:05,420
See this?

324
00:16:07,500 --> 00:16:10,060
Look. Abalone, razor shells,

325
00:16:10,860 --> 00:16:12,580
and prawns.

326
00:16:14,260 --> 00:16:17,260
I'll blanch them

327
00:16:17,380 --> 00:16:18,600
with ginger and cooking wine.

328
00:16:19,220 --> 00:16:20,980
I even bought some ham.

329
00:16:22,220 --> 00:16:24,700
Steam everything for 15 minutes.

330
00:16:24,700 --> 00:16:26,060
Pour out the extra liquid afterward.

331
00:16:26,420 --> 00:16:28,820
That's enough. Stop making me jealous.

332
00:16:29,140 --> 00:16:31,140
I want to fly back to Shanghai
right now.

333
00:16:31,340 --> 00:16:33,220
How come you always
cook all this good stuff

334
00:16:33,220 --> 00:16:34,580
when I'm not around?

335
00:16:35,488 --> 00:16:36,940
I'm celebrating getting my job back.

336
00:16:37,022 --> 00:16:39,022
Of course, I'm going to
treat myself a little.

337
00:16:39,050 --> 00:16:40,960
Lu Ze and you disappeared
on a team-building trip

338
00:16:40,977 --> 00:16:41,933
without saying a word.

339
00:16:42,533 --> 00:16:43,540
Don't even get me started.

340
00:16:43,540 --> 00:16:45,340
I thought I was getting a free vacation

341
00:16:45,340 --> 00:16:46,260
and lucking out.

342
00:16:46,466 --> 00:16:48,380
Turns out I was the one
who got the raw deal.

343
00:16:48,620 --> 00:16:49,622
(Wang Ruo Hai is in charge)
When you get back,

344
00:16:49,622 --> 00:16:51,300
(of the Shanlifang IPO)
I'll make it again for you.

345
00:16:51,300 --> 00:16:52,100
Is that okay?

346
00:16:53,140 --> 00:16:55,340
Fei, I'm hanging up.

347
00:16:55,540 --> 00:16:56,900
We're going to get dinner.

348
00:16:57,980 --> 00:16:58,740
Go ahead.

349
00:16:59,260 --> 00:17:00,700
Hang up for me. My hands are wet.

350
00:17:01,940 --> 00:17:02,660
Bye.

351
00:17:06,020 --> 00:17:08,700
♪Zhen fell in love with Qiang♪

352
00:17:09,260 --> 00:17:13,060
♪On a starry night♪

353
00:17:15,180 --> 00:17:17,740
♪An airplane flew across the sky♪

354
00:17:41,288 --> 00:17:42,266
You said

355
00:17:42,320 --> 00:17:44,540
that if Qian Fei found out
Wang Ruohai was at Shanlifang,

356
00:17:44,540 --> 00:17:45,822
she might not return to Hejing.

357
00:17:45,844 --> 00:17:47,340
Now that she's joined the project team,

358
00:17:47,340 --> 00:17:48,555
why are you keeping it from her?

359
00:17:48,580 --> 00:17:50,460
I'm worried she'll back out

360
00:17:50,460 --> 00:17:51,460
once she finds out.

361
00:17:51,980 --> 00:17:53,700
You have no idea how hard it was for her

362
00:17:53,700 --> 00:17:54,540
to get into this team.

363
00:17:54,780 --> 00:17:56,940
Even so, you should tell her.

364
00:17:58,244 --> 00:18:00,410
If she knows you knew all along
and didn't say anything,

365
00:18:00,420 --> 00:18:02,010
good luck talking your way
out of that one.

366
00:18:02,020 --> 00:18:03,470
You think I can't smooth things over?

367
00:18:03,580 --> 00:18:05,300
You think I'm wrong, don't you?

368
00:18:06,300 --> 00:18:07,740
No. Absolutely not.

369
00:18:07,780 --> 00:18:09,540
How could I think you're wrong?

370
00:18:09,780 --> 00:18:11,500
You're right. You're always right.

371
00:18:11,580 --> 00:18:12,820
How could you ever be wrong?

372
00:18:14,300 --> 00:18:15,540
Cheers.

373
00:18:15,822 --> 00:18:17,980
Thanks to Heaven for getting you back
into the workforce.

374
00:18:24,020 --> 00:18:25,020
Have some meat.

375
00:18:26,020 --> 00:18:26,860
Good, right?

376
00:18:28,220 --> 00:18:30,220
This is delicious.

377
00:18:30,860 --> 00:18:32,580
I love cooking for people like you.

378
00:18:32,700 --> 00:18:33,580
It makes me so happy.

379
00:18:33,711 --> 00:18:35,260
Your actions were a pretty honest review

380
00:18:35,380 --> 00:18:36,500
of my cooking.

381
00:18:36,700 --> 00:18:38,500
Why would I rate your cooking?

382
00:18:38,622 --> 00:18:40,260
You cooked for Wang Ruohai for years.

383
00:18:40,300 --> 00:18:41,180
Didn't he praise you?

384
00:18:41,311 --> 00:18:43,133
We already broke up. Don't bring him up.

385
00:18:43,177 --> 00:18:44,760
You should've broken up a long time ago.

386
00:18:44,780 --> 00:18:46,780
You two were never right for each other.

387
00:18:47,940 --> 00:18:49,420
From my life experience,

388
00:18:49,733 --> 00:18:51,020
if you're looking for a husband,

389
00:18:51,140 --> 00:18:53,400
you should find someone
who appreciates your strengths,

390
00:18:53,410 --> 00:18:54,980
someone who satisfies your taste buds,

391
00:18:55,111 --> 00:18:57,088
and someone you can happily
share meals with.

392
00:19:00,100 --> 00:19:02,980
You put this paste
into your stir-fried eggplant.

393
00:19:03,100 --> 00:19:03,860
It's really good.

394
00:19:04,200 --> 00:19:05,980
You should make it more often.
I like it.

395
00:19:08,200 --> 00:19:09,860
(Li Yifei: Authentic
Da Hong Pao Tea Egg)

396
00:19:09,860 --> 00:19:11,540
Uh. Didn't I hide it from you?

397
00:19:11,660 --> 00:19:12,540
How come?

398
00:19:12,733 --> 00:19:15,088
It's my first time doing this.
I'm still figuring it out.

399
00:19:15,420 --> 00:19:17,020
(What is this? It smells incredible.)

400
00:19:17,444 --> 00:19:19,777
(I've changed my mind.
I don't want those extra dishes.)

401
00:19:19,800 --> 00:19:20,822
I want this instead.

402
00:19:21,900 --> 00:19:22,740
What's on your mind?

403
00:19:26,020 --> 00:19:27,100
By your logic,

404
00:19:27,100 --> 00:19:28,355
your life experience means

405
00:19:28,422 --> 00:19:30,940
you should find a boyfriend
who thinks your instant noodles

406
00:19:30,940 --> 00:19:31,660
taste amazing.

407
00:19:32,100 --> 00:19:33,660
Instant noodles aren't healthy.

408
00:19:33,740 --> 00:19:35,500
If I can't cook,
I can still order takeout.

409
00:19:37,740 --> 00:19:39,140
Put away the leftovers.

410
00:19:39,180 --> 00:19:41,060
I'll wash all the dishes.

411
00:19:41,222 --> 00:19:42,420
Why are you being so nice?

412
00:19:42,860 --> 00:19:44,380
Come over again soon.

413
00:19:44,380 --> 00:19:45,500
I'll cook for you.

414
00:19:46,140 --> 00:19:48,420
You just want someone
to do your dishes for free.

415
00:19:49,380 --> 00:19:51,900
Fine. I can't keep mooching off
your cooking every time.

416
00:20:05,860 --> 00:20:07,022
Alright. I'll clean these up.

417
00:20:07,700 --> 00:20:09,260
It's all yours, then.

418
00:20:09,820 --> 00:20:10,780
Go rest.

419
00:20:20,420 --> 00:20:21,780
(I made too much for dinner.)

420
00:20:21,790 --> 00:20:23,550
(If you haven't eaten yet,
you can come back.)

421
00:20:23,580 --> 00:20:25,160
(Wouldn't want the food to go to waste.)

422
00:20:28,580 --> 00:20:31,060
(In the spirit of doing our part
for the planet,)

423
00:20:31,380 --> 00:20:33,380
(I may reluctantly come back)

424
00:20:33,380 --> 00:20:35,420
(and help solve
this food surplus crisis.)

425
00:20:40,220 --> 00:20:41,340
(No need.)

426
00:20:41,540 --> 00:20:43,140
(The stray dogs downstairs are hungry.)

427
00:20:44,220 --> 00:20:46,040
(Qian Fei)

428
00:20:46,070 --> 00:20:47,740
(Hands off! They're all mine.)

429
00:20:51,620 --> 00:20:53,660
(Why are you fighting with dogs
over food?)

430
00:20:56,860 --> 00:20:59,180
(A single man like me
is more pitiful than a stray.)

431
00:21:01,020 --> 00:21:02,740
(Fine. The dog food's all yours.)

432
00:21:02,740 --> 00:21:04,180
I'm fast, right?

433
00:21:07,180 --> 00:21:08,340
What are you laughing about?

434
00:21:09,780 --> 00:21:10,380
Uh.

435
00:21:11,460 --> 00:21:14,140
I just snagged a pack of tissues
on a flash sale. So cheap.

436
00:21:14,933 --> 00:21:16,140
That goofy grin on your face.

437
00:21:16,700 --> 00:21:18,540
I bought this for you.
Remember to use it.

438
00:21:19,980 --> 00:21:20,740
I love you.

439
00:21:21,420 --> 00:21:23,540
It works really well.
Take good care of yourself.

440
00:21:24,340 --> 00:21:25,140
Alright.

441
00:21:28,540 --> 00:21:30,420
Well, you've been broken up
for some time.

442
00:21:31,020 --> 00:21:32,660
Have you thought about

443
00:21:32,660 --> 00:21:34,700
looking for someone new?

444
00:21:35,940 --> 00:21:36,900
Not interested.

445
00:21:37,540 --> 00:21:38,900
How can you not be interested?

446
00:21:38,900 --> 00:21:39,980
You're still young.

447
00:21:40,155 --> 00:21:41,380
You can't swear off dating

448
00:21:41,380 --> 00:21:42,660
just because of one jerk.

449
00:21:44,780 --> 00:21:46,100
You're acting weird.

450
00:21:46,111 --> 00:21:48,800
You don't worry about yourself,
but you're worried about me.

451
00:21:49,700 --> 00:21:50,220
I...

452
00:21:50,911 --> 00:21:52,740
Is there something
you're trying to tell me?

453
00:21:52,860 --> 00:21:54,111
Stop beating around the bush.

454
00:21:58,622 --> 00:22:00,355
Someone wants to take you out to a meal.

455
00:22:00,940 --> 00:22:01,500
Who?

456
00:22:04,980 --> 00:22:09,380
(Lujiazui Dongyuan Subdistrict Office)

457
00:22:09,380 --> 00:22:10,866
What are you treating me to today?

458
00:22:11,660 --> 00:22:13,420
Which girl are you texting this time?

459
00:22:13,420 --> 00:22:14,620
What girl?

460
00:22:14,688 --> 00:22:15,860
I'm not eating with you today.

461
00:22:16,377 --> 00:22:19,111
The landlady saved me some food.
I'm heading home to eat.

462
00:22:19,900 --> 00:22:21,340
You can't betray your friend.

463
00:22:21,422 --> 00:22:23,180
I told my mom
I wasn't going home for dinner.

464
00:22:23,190 --> 00:22:25,088
If I go back,
there won't be anything left to eat.

465
00:22:25,140 --> 00:22:27,850
Your mom is not going to let you starve.
What's there to worry about?

466
00:22:27,860 --> 00:22:30,060
I was just passing by to check on you.

467
00:22:31,020 --> 00:22:33,900
Seeing that you're still
sturdy, healthy,

468
00:22:33,980 --> 00:22:35,780
and rosy-cheeked, I can rest easy.

469
00:22:35,900 --> 00:22:36,700
Now go home and eat.

470
00:22:38,740 --> 00:22:41,260
Have you actually fallen
for your landlady?

471
00:22:42,660 --> 00:22:44,060
With my standards?

472
00:22:44,377 --> 00:22:45,540
You think I'd fall for her?

473
00:22:46,060 --> 00:22:47,700
You're too close to see it.

474
00:22:47,810 --> 00:22:48,980
Listen to my analysis.

475
00:22:49,260 --> 00:22:50,700
The last time I ate at your place,

476
00:22:50,777 --> 00:22:51,866
I thought something was off.

477
00:22:52,020 --> 00:22:53,660
Didn't you notice

478
00:22:53,670 --> 00:22:55,022
you two didn't use serving spoons?

479
00:22:55,460 --> 00:22:56,140
Did we not?

480
00:22:57,500 --> 00:22:58,300
I probably forgot.

481
00:22:59,820 --> 00:23:01,220
Fine. Then let me ask you this.

482
00:23:01,380 --> 00:23:02,660
When you drive,

483
00:23:02,660 --> 00:23:04,580
other than girls you like,

484
00:23:04,688 --> 00:23:06,580
you always make other women
sit in the back.

485
00:23:06,800 --> 00:23:08,260
And where does your landlady sit?

486
00:23:08,444 --> 00:23:10,155
Of course, she sits in the...

487
00:23:14,700 --> 00:23:15,700
Front passenger seat.

488
00:23:16,620 --> 00:23:17,140
Makes sense?

489
00:23:21,740 --> 00:23:22,820
You see,

490
00:23:22,820 --> 00:23:24,540
I borrowed this car from the steward.

491
00:23:24,780 --> 00:23:25,780
I'm not that particular.

492
00:23:26,244 --> 00:23:27,780
It has nothing to do with the car.

493
00:23:27,780 --> 00:23:29,020
It's about your subconscious.

494
00:23:30,020 --> 00:23:32,700
The fact that you're not even sure
whether you like her

495
00:23:32,700 --> 00:23:34,020
means you've fallen for her.

496
00:23:34,220 --> 00:23:35,140
Nonsense.

497
00:23:35,660 --> 00:23:37,140
You've been single all your life.

498
00:23:37,140 --> 00:23:39,380
And you're questioning
a love expert like me?

499
00:23:39,580 --> 00:23:41,511
Getting a little full of yourself,
aren't you?

500
00:23:42,340 --> 00:23:43,260
Go home and eat.

501
00:23:44,377 --> 00:23:46,060
Don't forget about the plan tomorrow.

502
00:23:46,340 --> 00:23:48,340
I know. You treat, and I pay.

503
00:23:48,620 --> 00:23:49,140
See you.

504
00:23:49,300 --> 00:23:49,700
Bye-bye.

505
00:23:50,500 --> 00:23:51,260
Me and him?

506
00:23:51,340 --> 00:23:52,340
No way.

507
00:23:53,540 --> 00:23:54,900
Why not?

508
00:23:55,780 --> 00:23:57,340
You know each other.

509
00:23:57,340 --> 00:23:58,100
And he said,

510
00:23:58,100 --> 00:23:59,740
to ease the awkwardness from before,

511
00:23:59,740 --> 00:24:01,500
he wants to take you out for a meal

512
00:24:01,740 --> 00:24:02,900
and apologize properly.

513
00:24:03,260 --> 00:24:04,540
I think it's a great opportunity.

514
00:24:04,540 --> 00:24:06,100
You can eat and get to know each other.

515
00:24:06,300 --> 00:24:08,100
If you get to know him more,
who knows...

516
00:24:10,060 --> 00:24:11,500
He never told me.

517
00:24:12,260 --> 00:24:13,660
He's probably shy.

518
00:24:14,540 --> 00:24:15,700
When did he tell you?

519
00:24:16,140 --> 00:24:18,740
He came to see me after work today.

520
00:24:19,340 --> 00:24:20,780
He was really sincere.

521
00:24:21,340 --> 00:24:22,900
He especially came to see you?

522
00:24:25,340 --> 00:24:26,300
I'm not going.

523
00:24:27,090 --> 00:24:28,140
I...

524
00:24:28,280 --> 00:24:28,940
I'm busy.

525
00:24:29,620 --> 00:24:31,660
Come on, it's the weekend tomorrow.

526
00:24:32,460 --> 00:24:34,060
I'm really not interested.

527
00:24:34,260 --> 00:24:35,780
Not even interested in a meal?

528
00:24:36,300 --> 00:24:37,620
If the conversation goes badly,

529
00:24:37,740 --> 00:24:39,260
just treat it as a free fancy meal.

530
00:24:40,020 --> 00:24:41,300
Free fancy meal?

531
00:24:42,460 --> 00:24:44,460
He's the one getting
three free meals a day.

532
00:24:47,940 --> 00:24:48,700
You have to go.

533
00:24:49,180 --> 00:24:51,380
I've cleared my schedule for tomorrow.

534
00:24:51,620 --> 00:24:53,220
I want a free fancy meal.

535
00:24:53,980 --> 00:24:55,020
Just the three of us?

536
00:24:55,488 --> 00:24:56,540
Oh, I forgot to tell you.

537
00:24:56,780 --> 00:24:57,500
Four people.

538
00:24:58,180 --> 00:24:59,500
You, me, Jun Cheng,

539
00:25:00,860 --> 00:25:01,380
and Li Yifei.

540
00:25:05,700 --> 00:25:07,700
He... Likes me?

541
00:25:08,740 --> 00:25:09,700
Is this a prank?

542
00:25:10,260 --> 00:25:11,540
What prank?

543
00:25:11,540 --> 00:25:14,100
He's a nice guy. Very sincere.

544
00:25:14,940 --> 00:25:16,260
Very sincere?

545
00:25:17,140 --> 00:25:19,780
That's why people need to
get to know each other.

546
00:25:23,540 --> 00:25:25,780
I... I can't.

547
00:25:26,444 --> 00:25:28,500
We're familiar with each other.
Why go out for a meal?

548
00:25:28,500 --> 00:25:29,700
Don't you think it's weird?

549
00:25:29,860 --> 00:25:31,900
Oh, come on. It's just a meal.

550
00:25:31,900 --> 00:25:33,580
Stop dragging it out.

551
00:25:33,660 --> 00:25:34,700
Are you going or not?

552
00:25:35,820 --> 00:25:37,900
Fine, fine. I'll listen to you.

553
00:25:38,460 --> 00:25:40,540
But just so we're clear.

554
00:25:40,540 --> 00:25:42,140
I'm only going for the free meal.

555
00:25:42,620 --> 00:25:44,020
Okay. As long as you go.

556
00:25:47,620 --> 00:25:48,740
What are you wearing tomorrow?

557
00:25:50,380 --> 00:25:51,020
No idea.

558
00:26:01,020 --> 00:26:02,780
How old are these clothes?

559
00:26:03,200 --> 00:26:05,060
You wore this back in university,
didn't you?

560
00:26:06,500 --> 00:26:07,300
This one.

561
00:26:07,660 --> 00:26:10,140
It's stretched out.
You're still keeping it?

562
00:26:13,700 --> 00:26:14,620
Oh my goodness.

563
00:26:16,140 --> 00:26:16,780
What is this?

564
00:26:17,540 --> 00:26:18,620
Barbie pink?

565
00:26:19,700 --> 00:26:20,620
Flamingo?

566
00:26:21,020 --> 00:26:22,260
How old are you?

567
00:26:25,260 --> 00:26:26,740
What's wrong with it?

568
00:26:28,100 --> 00:26:28,780
And this?

569
00:26:29,220 --> 00:26:30,660
A dragon fruit?

570
00:26:32,020 --> 00:26:33,020
What even is all this?

571
00:26:33,180 --> 00:26:33,740
Please.

572
00:26:33,740 --> 00:26:35,380
Throw out every piece in this color.

573
00:26:37,460 --> 00:26:39,500
Are you helping me pick an outfit,

574
00:26:39,500 --> 00:26:41,420
or sorting out my wardrobe?

575
00:26:44,580 --> 00:26:45,580
This one isn't bad.

576
00:26:46,940 --> 00:26:48,300
You actually bought this brand?

577
00:26:48,733 --> 00:26:49,980
It's a gift from Jingjing.

578
00:26:51,940 --> 00:26:52,980
I knew it.

579
00:26:54,020 --> 00:26:54,540
This works.

580
00:26:54,620 --> 00:26:55,488
Let's go with this.

581
00:26:56,340 --> 00:26:56,740
But...

582
00:26:57,780 --> 00:26:58,700
Puff sleeves?

583
00:26:58,940 --> 00:27:00,620
Isn't that inappropriate
for the occasion?

584
00:27:01,780 --> 00:27:02,660
Why wouldn't it be?

585
00:27:02,780 --> 00:27:04,044
What's wrong with puff sleeves?

586
00:27:04,180 --> 00:27:05,300
A young man

587
00:27:05,420 --> 00:27:06,980
sincerely invited you to a meal.

588
00:27:07,260 --> 00:27:08,780
Show some effort, okay?

589
00:27:13,500 --> 00:27:14,380
This is the one.

590
00:27:14,540 --> 00:27:15,940
I don't see it that way.

591
00:27:17,380 --> 00:27:20,300
Alright, it's just a meal.

592
00:27:20,580 --> 00:27:22,660
I'll keep the conversation going.

593
00:27:22,660 --> 00:27:24,380
It won't be awkward.

594
00:27:24,540 --> 00:27:25,660
Okay.

595
00:27:26,022 --> 00:27:26,980
I'm counting on you.

596
00:27:27,260 --> 00:27:28,740
It's getting late. I should get going.

597
00:27:28,980 --> 00:27:30,100
There won't be any cabs left.

598
00:27:30,380 --> 00:27:30,660
Okay.

599
00:27:32,420 --> 00:27:33,020
I...

600
00:27:34,133 --> 00:27:35,100
What a coincidence.

601
00:27:35,100 --> 00:27:36,100
When did you get home?

602
00:27:37,780 --> 00:27:39,060
You didn't make a sound.

603
00:27:45,980 --> 00:27:46,688
I'm leaving.

604
00:27:46,940 --> 00:27:47,540
Okay. Bye.

605
00:27:47,540 --> 00:27:48,940
Bye. Take care.

606
00:28:02,940 --> 00:28:03,460
Come in.

607
00:28:05,420 --> 00:28:05,820
I...

608
00:28:12,422 --> 00:28:13,377
You're not planning to

609
00:28:13,580 --> 00:28:15,700
wear this, are you?

610
00:28:16,380 --> 00:28:17,540
What's wrong with it? Can't I?

611
00:28:17,980 --> 00:28:18,700
This?

612
00:28:20,060 --> 00:28:21,020
Seriously?

613
00:28:22,060 --> 00:28:23,740
You'll look like a turkey.

614
00:28:23,940 --> 00:28:24,580
Let go.

615
00:28:24,820 --> 00:28:25,660
You are a turkey.

616
00:28:26,020 --> 00:28:26,620
I'm not going.

617
00:28:27,700 --> 00:28:29,020
That's right.

618
00:28:29,420 --> 00:28:31,220
I thought you'd been busy
with work lately.

619
00:28:31,300 --> 00:28:33,577
Turns out you've been thinking
about this stuff instead.

620
00:28:33,660 --> 00:28:34,300
Look at you.

621
00:28:34,400 --> 00:28:36,520
You just broke up,
and now you're going on a blind date.

622
00:28:36,533 --> 00:28:38,410
You leave one jerk to find another one.

623
00:28:38,420 --> 00:28:39,700
Aren't you tired?

624
00:28:41,644 --> 00:28:43,650
Good. If you're not going,
then I can finally relax.

625
00:28:43,660 --> 00:28:44,500
Li Yifei,

626
00:28:45,060 --> 00:28:46,700
do you have split personalities?

627
00:28:47,620 --> 00:28:48,900
Are you testing me?

628
00:28:49,500 --> 00:28:50,460
Why would I test you?

629
00:28:51,380 --> 00:28:52,620
You're the one who invited me.

630
00:28:52,620 --> 00:28:54,377
And you're the one
calling yourself a jerk.

631
00:28:54,500 --> 00:28:56,540
Messing with me at home wasn't enough,

632
00:28:56,860 --> 00:28:58,820
so you went to ask Dang Yu
to arrange a meal?

633
00:28:59,140 --> 00:29:00,620
You said you liked me?

634
00:29:01,340 --> 00:29:02,660
Is messing with me fun?

635
00:29:02,740 --> 00:29:03,620
Is it amusing?

636
00:29:04,100 --> 00:29:05,420
Get out. I don't want to see you.

637
00:29:06,020 --> 00:29:07,100
No, wait. Hold on.

638
00:29:07,100 --> 00:29:07,660
Out!

639
00:29:07,660 --> 00:29:08,300
Hold on.

640
00:29:09,740 --> 00:29:11,460
I said I was a jerk?

641
00:29:12,020 --> 00:29:13,180
I like you?

642
00:29:22,140 --> 00:29:23,220
I get it now.

643
00:29:25,380 --> 00:29:26,500
I get it.

644
00:29:26,620 --> 00:29:28,060
Are you insane?

645
00:29:48,580 --> 00:29:49,660
Jun Cheng invited you.

646
00:29:50,140 --> 00:29:51,140
Didn't I tell you?

647
00:29:51,700 --> 00:29:52,740
Who did you think it was?

648
00:30:00,380 --> 00:30:01,660
So it was all a misunderstanding.

649
00:30:02,260 --> 00:30:03,260
A misunderstanding.

650
00:30:07,180 --> 00:30:08,740
I've never been wronged like this

651
00:30:09,180 --> 00:30:12,260
in my entire life.

652
00:30:13,220 --> 00:30:14,980
Poor me.

653
00:30:14,980 --> 00:30:16,980
There's no way

654
00:30:16,980 --> 00:30:19,260
I could clear my name.

655
00:30:20,980 --> 00:30:22,860
Aren't you going to make it up to me?

656
00:30:49,500 --> 00:30:51,020
I'm so sorry.

657
00:30:52,060 --> 00:30:53,220
It was a misunderstanding.

658
00:30:53,220 --> 00:30:54,800
I thought you were inviting me
to a meal.

659
00:30:54,822 --> 00:30:55,888
I thought you had...

660
00:30:56,140 --> 00:30:57,340
Feelings for you?

661
00:30:57,500 --> 00:30:58,060
Yeah.

662
00:30:58,466 --> 00:30:59,300
You overthought it.

663
00:30:59,755 --> 00:31:01,100
That's definitely overthinking.

664
00:31:02,740 --> 00:31:03,380
It's fine.

665
00:31:03,444 --> 00:31:05,850
When someone's always on your mind,
misunderstandings happen.

666
00:31:05,860 --> 00:31:06,444
I understand.

667
00:31:06,711 --> 00:31:07,733
What are you talking about?

668
00:31:07,900 --> 00:31:10,700
Are you saying I have feelings for you?

669
00:31:11,380 --> 00:31:12,940
You're overthinking now. I really don't.

670
00:31:13,540 --> 00:31:14,140
You see,

671
00:31:14,311 --> 00:31:16,777
I don't have the time or the energy
to like anyone right now.

672
00:31:16,780 --> 00:31:17,620
Don't worry.

673
00:31:17,740 --> 00:31:20,740
I swear. If I have the slightest
improper intentions toward you,

674
00:31:20,760 --> 00:31:21,920
may lightning strike me down.

675
00:31:21,940 --> 00:31:22,700
Fine, fine, fine.

676
00:31:23,580 --> 00:31:24,660
That's a bit much.

677
00:31:25,540 --> 00:31:26,980
I'll take your word for it.

678
00:31:27,780 --> 00:31:29,180
But let me add one thing.

679
00:31:30,460 --> 00:31:32,500
Jun doesn't like you either.

680
00:31:33,020 --> 00:31:34,620
Jun doesn't like anyone.

681
00:31:35,100 --> 00:31:37,180
He's only interested in gaming.

682
00:31:38,200 --> 00:31:40,222
When he said he wanted
to treat everyone to a meal,

683
00:31:40,260 --> 00:31:41,900
he meant exactly that.

684
00:31:42,220 --> 00:31:42,660
Got it?

685
00:31:43,420 --> 00:31:44,100
Got it.

686
00:31:44,580 --> 00:31:45,780
The same goes for Dang Yu.

687
00:31:45,900 --> 00:31:47,020
She has too many side hustles.

688
00:31:47,180 --> 00:31:48,890
It's easy to misread
other people's kindness.

689
00:31:51,660 --> 00:31:53,980
Now that I know
you're not interested in me,

690
00:31:54,940 --> 00:31:55,980
I can finally relax.

691
00:31:56,700 --> 00:31:58,100
(What does that mean?)

692
00:31:58,260 --> 00:31:59,220
(What's wrong with me?)

693
00:32:00,420 --> 00:32:03,060
You know, we're landlady and tenant,

694
00:32:03,220 --> 00:32:05,220
plus colleagues.

695
00:32:05,420 --> 00:32:06,660
It's more than enough for me.

696
00:32:06,800 --> 00:32:08,340
If there's anything else on top of that,

697
00:32:08,780 --> 00:32:10,140
I'd completely lose it.

698
00:32:12,380 --> 00:32:13,220
Come on, master.

699
00:32:13,540 --> 00:32:14,580
This toast is for you.

700
00:32:14,860 --> 00:32:15,780
After this drink,

701
00:32:15,940 --> 00:32:16,780
let's pretend

702
00:32:16,820 --> 00:32:17,860
nothing happened tonight.

703
00:32:18,260 --> 00:32:18,580
Cheers.

704
00:32:24,180 --> 00:32:25,220
Another game.

705
00:32:25,540 --> 00:32:26,380
Still playing?

706
00:32:26,460 --> 00:32:26,900
Come on.

707
00:32:27,020 --> 00:32:27,620
Still drinking?

708
00:32:27,740 --> 00:32:28,060
Hurry.

709
00:32:28,260 --> 00:32:28,980
Come on.

710
00:32:29,140 --> 00:32:30,020
Let's play a game.

711
00:32:30,980 --> 00:32:31,580
Ready.

712
00:32:31,580 --> 00:32:32,980
Three, two, one. Look over here.

713
00:32:33,460 --> 00:32:34,300
You lost.

714
00:32:34,320 --> 00:32:37,610
♪Hey, you, you, you,
why is it you again?♪

715
00:32:37,910 --> 00:32:41,940
♪Always stumbling upon
my little secrets♪

716
00:32:42,340 --> 00:32:44,540
♪Falling on my brows, my lashes♪

717
00:32:44,540 --> 00:32:46,360
♪Even the strands by my mouth♪

718
00:32:46,360 --> 00:32:49,220
♪Like my favorite kitten♪

719
00:32:49,220 --> 00:32:51,030
♪On a rainy spring afternoon♪

720
00:32:51,030 --> 00:32:55,690
♪Hey, you, you, you,
why is it you again?♪

721
00:32:55,690 --> 00:32:59,480
You effortlessly awaken
my protective instincts♪

722
00:32:59,760 --> 00:33:01,900
♪Hitting all my little thoughts♪

723
00:33:01,900 --> 00:33:03,820
♪My doubts, and my temper♪

724
00:33:04,100 --> 00:33:07,060
♪Like my favorite beer
and fried chicken in autumn♪

725
00:33:07,060 --> 00:33:08,670
♪Or spicy boiled fish in winter♪

726
00:33:08,970 --> 00:33:13,140
♪Why is it you again?
That sweet way you speak♪

727
00:33:13,370 --> 00:33:17,450
♪As if the whole world knows
my mind is full of you♪

728
00:33:17,730 --> 00:33:21,900
♪Why is it still you?
That secret smile behind your cool facade♪

729
00:33:22,100 --> 00:33:26,130
♪I might as well play along.
Let me protect you♪

730
00:33:26,430 --> 00:33:30,560
♪Why is it always you?
The smile at the corner of your lips♪

731
00:33:30,850 --> 00:33:33,222
♪Before I knew it,
the words blurted out♪

732
00:33:33,222 --> 00:33:35,220
♪I like you. I only like you♪

733
00:33:35,260 --> 00:33:37,380
Landlady, I must say,

734
00:33:39,060 --> 00:33:40,860
you're actually pretty cute
when you're drunk.

735
00:33:41,580 --> 00:33:43,020
You're nothing like your normal self.

736
00:33:43,420 --> 00:33:45,780
Normally, you're too much
of a tough girl.

737
00:33:46,140 --> 00:33:46,860
It's a little...

738
00:33:50,180 --> 00:33:50,980
Asleep?

739
00:33:57,660 --> 00:33:58,700
Such a lightweight.

740
00:33:58,822 --> 00:34:00,380
Yet you still have the nerve
to talk big.

741
00:34:02,060 --> 00:34:03,540
I'll give you a hand one more time.

742
00:34:04,300 --> 00:34:06,380
Come on. Put your arm around me.

743
00:34:06,460 --> 00:34:06,940
Good.

744
00:34:07,540 --> 00:34:08,260
Let's go.

745
00:34:08,260 --> 00:34:08,860
Up we go.

746
00:34:09,620 --> 00:34:11,620
One, two, three.

747
00:35:02,580 --> 00:35:04,780
Why do I suddenly think
the landlady looks pretty?

748
00:35:10,100 --> 00:35:10,780
It's the alcohol.

749
00:35:12,220 --> 00:35:13,460
It has to be the alcohol.

750
00:35:13,644 --> 00:35:14,840
I must have alcohol poisoning.

751
00:35:15,620 --> 00:35:16,260
No way.

752
00:35:36,820 --> 00:35:38,500
(Yifei)

753
00:35:43,540 --> 00:35:44,100
Hello?

754
00:35:45,060 --> 00:35:47,180
In the middle of the night?
What's wrong?

755
00:35:48,060 --> 00:35:48,940
I'm in trouble.

756
00:35:50,260 --> 00:35:51,220
You were right.

757
00:35:54,540 --> 00:35:56,580
I think I've fallen for my landlady.

758
00:36:15,933 --> 00:36:16,980
What are you looking at?

759
00:36:18,088 --> 00:36:19,620
Why aren't you wearing the turkey?

760
00:36:20,700 --> 00:36:22,140
Didn't I tell you yesterday?

761
00:36:22,340 --> 00:36:24,488
Don't bring it up again
after the drinking session.

762
00:36:24,860 --> 00:36:26,340
Alright. I won't.

763
00:36:28,700 --> 00:36:29,540
But honestly,

764
00:36:30,380 --> 00:36:32,020
you look pretty nice dressed like this.

765
00:36:33,620 --> 00:36:35,740
This is how I usually dress
when I take the bus.

766
00:36:36,820 --> 00:36:38,340
Good. This is the real you.

767
00:36:39,060 --> 00:36:39,500
Let's go.

768
00:36:41,140 --> 00:36:43,020
Do you know
how drunk you got last night?

769
00:36:43,333 --> 00:36:45,380
I was really sorry about
what happened last time.

770
00:36:45,940 --> 00:36:47,711
Today, I'd like to
properly apologize to you,

771
00:36:47,720 --> 00:36:49,300
Big Sister Qian and Big Sister Dang.

772
00:36:49,488 --> 00:36:50,888
Sorry for causing you trouble.

773
00:36:52,060 --> 00:36:52,340
Hey.

774
00:36:52,350 --> 00:36:53,500
Who are you calling big sister?

775
00:36:54,140 --> 00:36:54,620
Miss.

776
00:36:56,380 --> 00:36:58,100
Pretty Miss. Pretty Miss.

777
00:36:59,100 --> 00:37:00,620
I'd almost forgotten about that.

778
00:37:00,700 --> 00:37:01,380
That's great.

779
00:37:02,660 --> 00:37:03,420
Sit.

780
00:37:08,260 --> 00:37:10,180
Let's order. See what you want.

781
00:37:11,266 --> 00:37:13,111
Qian Fei, you choose.
I'm fine with anything.

782
00:37:17,820 --> 00:37:19,300
You take a look too. My treat.

783
00:37:19,900 --> 00:37:20,860
That's rare.

784
00:37:21,100 --> 00:37:22,700
Jun has never treated me.

785
00:37:23,260 --> 00:37:24,180
That's because

786
00:37:24,244 --> 00:37:25,540
his mom keeps all his money.

787
00:37:29,222 --> 00:37:30,140
What are you playing?

788
00:37:32,822 --> 00:37:35,177
She's just playing a game.
Don't stick your nose in.

789
00:37:35,180 --> 00:37:36,780
Done. Take a look.

790
00:37:37,340 --> 00:37:38,180
You decide.

791
00:37:38,220 --> 00:37:39,340
I don't dare order.

792
00:37:39,380 --> 00:37:40,410
Then I'll place the order.

793
00:37:46,340 --> 00:37:47,100
What are you doing?

794
00:37:47,420 --> 00:37:47,820
Wait.

795
00:37:48,220 --> 00:37:49,660
Hold on. Your username.

796
00:37:50,220 --> 00:37:51,020
Your username.

797
00:37:52,177 --> 00:37:53,260
What are you doing?

798
00:37:53,300 --> 00:37:54,120
What are you doing?

799
00:37:55,140 --> 00:37:55,820
Hey. Hey.

800
00:37:55,820 --> 00:37:56,580
What are you doing?

801
00:37:56,688 --> 00:37:58,100
- Let go.
- What are you doing?

802
00:37:58,100 --> 00:37:59,780
- What are you doing? Calm down.
- Wait...

803
00:37:59,790 --> 00:38:00,790
What are you trying to do?

804
00:38:00,800 --> 00:38:01,140
She is...

805
00:38:01,380 --> 00:38:02,460
We're in public.

806
00:38:03,140 --> 00:38:03,700
She is...

807
00:38:03,844 --> 00:38:05,420
Whoever she is, you can't act like this.

808
00:38:05,420 --> 00:38:05,860
She is...

809
00:38:06,466 --> 00:38:08,180
Calm yourself down.
This is a public place.

810
00:38:08,180 --> 00:38:09,720
Want to get thrown over
my shoulder again?

811
00:38:09,733 --> 00:38:11,940
She is Po Ming!

812
00:38:12,755 --> 00:38:13,820
I'm going to beat you up!

813
00:38:14,340 --> 00:38:15,340
She's your idol?

814
00:38:15,620 --> 00:38:17,660
Po Ming! Yes.
I watch her streams every day.

815
00:38:17,670 --> 00:38:19,740
- Even so, calm down.
- He watches my streams.

816
00:38:19,860 --> 00:38:21,220
I can't calm down.

817
00:38:22,180 --> 00:38:23,660
We're in public. Keep it together.

818
00:38:23,660 --> 00:38:24,660
Look how excited he is.

819
00:38:25,140 --> 00:38:25,740
I'm...

820
00:38:27,220 --> 00:38:28,140
I'm Grand Chancellor.

821
00:38:28,140 --> 00:38:29,140
He's your fan.

822
00:38:29,860 --> 00:38:30,380
What?

823
00:38:31,060 --> 00:38:31,900
Grand Chancellor.

824
00:38:32,180 --> 00:38:33,220
You're Grand Chancellor?

825
00:38:33,420 --> 00:38:34,460
Yes, Grand Chancellor.

826
00:38:37,980 --> 00:38:38,460
Wait.

827
00:38:39,177 --> 00:38:41,422
- The one who joined the team.
- Keep it together.

828
00:38:41,480 --> 00:38:42,420
You met each other now.

829
00:38:42,420 --> 00:38:43,820
Alright. Let's focus on the meal.

830
00:38:45,180 --> 00:38:47,220
Wait. How could he be a woman?

831
00:38:47,220 --> 00:38:48,620
What's wrong with her being a woman?

832
00:38:49,155 --> 00:38:50,340
I'm going to the restroom.

833
00:38:52,380 --> 00:38:52,780
Look.

834
00:38:53,540 --> 00:38:54,460
Calm down.

835
00:38:54,660 --> 00:38:55,900
I can't calm down.

836
00:38:55,900 --> 00:38:57,600
Do you want there to be a next time
or not?

837
00:38:57,666 --> 00:38:58,980
Don't get yourself thrown over
her shoulder again.

838
00:38:58,980 --> 00:38:59,660
Calm down.

839
00:38:59,733 --> 00:39:00,340
Oh my goodness.

840
00:39:01,660 --> 00:39:03,060
Alright. Calm yourself.

841
00:39:04,340 --> 00:39:05,140
It's okay.

842
00:39:05,140 --> 00:39:07,340
I must abscond. Dear, enjoy the meal.

843
00:39:07,340 --> 00:39:08,644
I'll make it up to you later.

844
00:39:08,660 --> 00:39:09,740
Easy, easy.

845
00:39:09,740 --> 00:39:10,260
Calm down.

846
00:39:10,260 --> 00:39:11,820
- Easy. Life is full of surprises.
-Um...

847
00:39:12,780 --> 00:39:13,580
She's gone.

848
00:39:13,580 --> 00:39:14,060
See?

849
00:39:14,580 --> 00:39:15,300
I told you.

850
00:39:15,740 --> 00:39:16,600
You scared her off.

851
00:39:16,688 --> 00:39:18,580
I told you not to get so worked up.

852
00:39:19,740 --> 00:39:20,460
You guys eat.

853
00:39:20,600 --> 00:39:21,500
What are you doing?

854
00:39:22,000 --> 00:39:24,488
Don't get yourself thrown over
her shoulder again.

855
00:39:30,860 --> 00:39:31,540
Po Ming Bro,

856
00:39:31,800 --> 00:39:33,711
where are you going?
We haven't eaten yet.

857
00:39:34,577 --> 00:39:36,180
I've got a side job. I totally forgot.

858
00:39:36,340 --> 00:39:37,140
I'll drive you.

859
00:39:37,420 --> 00:39:39,060
No need. I'll grab a cab myself.

860
00:39:39,060 --> 00:39:39,700
A side job?

861
00:39:40,100 --> 00:39:41,940
You're a receptionist, a bartender,

862
00:39:41,940 --> 00:39:42,700
and a streamer.

863
00:39:43,100 --> 00:39:44,340
You still have another job.

864
00:39:44,620 --> 00:39:45,980
You're amazing.

865
00:39:46,700 --> 00:39:48,900
Don't be impressed. I'm amazing.

866
00:39:51,300 --> 00:39:51,900
Po Ming!

867
00:39:52,380 --> 00:39:53,540
What?

868
00:39:56,444 --> 00:39:57,377
My admiration for you

869
00:39:57,380 --> 00:39:59,260
is like the endless waves
of the mighty river.

870
00:39:59,260 --> 00:40:01,990
Like Yellow River, it flows on without
an end and is impossible to stop.

871
00:40:02,300 --> 00:40:03,220
I never imagined that

872
00:40:03,230 --> 00:40:04,970
the legend I've
dreamed about day and night

873
00:40:04,980 --> 00:40:07,500
would actually be standing
right in front of me.

874
00:40:07,900 --> 00:40:08,780
My admiration

875
00:40:08,780 --> 00:40:11,060
has broken free from gravity
and shot straight into the sky.

876
00:40:11,060 --> 00:40:12,540
You're like the bright moon in the sky.

877
00:40:12,540 --> 00:40:13,540
Unattainable!

878
00:40:14,140 --> 00:40:14,780
Po Ming!

879
00:40:14,780 --> 00:40:15,700
What are you doing?

880
00:40:17,780 --> 00:40:18,900
I memorized that speech

881
00:40:19,180 --> 00:40:20,740
a long time ago.

882
00:40:20,900 --> 00:40:22,200
I've always dreamed that one day

883
00:40:22,266 --> 00:40:23,940
I'd be able to say it to you in person.

884
00:40:24,100 --> 00:40:24,540
Yes!

885
00:40:26,955 --> 00:40:28,350
- Please.
- What's wrong with him?

886
00:40:28,380 --> 00:40:30,780
Give me a chance to get up close
and personal with my idol.

887
00:40:30,940 --> 00:40:32,180
Please let me drive you.

888
00:40:37,180 --> 00:40:40,300
I've received your admiration.

889
00:40:40,700 --> 00:40:42,020
You should head home early.

890
00:40:42,020 --> 00:40:42,620
Po Ming!

891
00:40:43,900 --> 00:40:45,780
Please let me drive you. Please!

892
00:40:47,220 --> 00:40:48,100
Where's your car?

893
00:40:48,380 --> 00:40:49,020
Over there.

894
00:40:49,740 --> 00:40:50,660
Let's go.

895
00:40:52,380 --> 00:40:53,220
Where are you going?

896
00:40:53,711 --> 00:40:54,740
Leave this place first.

897
00:41:00,020 --> 00:41:02,420
I've wanted to tell you this
several times.

898
00:41:02,420 --> 00:41:04,380
But I felt sorry for you,
so I held back.

899
00:41:05,860 --> 00:41:08,660
Gui Lili isn't living
at my place anymore.

900
00:41:09,220 --> 00:41:10,660
And we're both single.

901
00:41:11,288 --> 00:41:13,422
If we keep sharing an apartment
like this,

902
00:41:13,460 --> 00:41:13,820
uh,

903
00:41:13,860 --> 00:41:14,940
it's really inconvenient.

904
00:41:15,380 --> 00:41:17,460
Is it? I think it's pretty convenient.

905
00:41:17,620 --> 00:41:18,980
That's just what you think.

906
00:41:18,980 --> 00:41:20,380
Other people won't see it that way.

907
00:41:20,533 --> 00:41:22,644
We're both going to work
at Shanlifang tomorrow,

908
00:41:23,300 --> 00:41:24,780
and we're on the same project team.

909
00:41:24,780 --> 00:41:26,260
Being colleagues is one thing,

910
00:41:26,700 --> 00:41:28,660
but if people find out
we're living together,

911
00:41:29,020 --> 00:41:30,100
it's going to be awkward.

912
00:41:30,700 --> 00:41:32,900
Just ignore them, right?

913
00:41:33,500 --> 00:41:34,420
Hold on, landlady.

914
00:41:34,700 --> 00:41:35,860
Judging by what you're saying,

915
00:41:35,860 --> 00:41:37,740
it sounds like you're abandoning
your master.

916
00:41:39,460 --> 00:41:41,740
I helped you get your job back, didn't I?

917
00:41:42,580 --> 00:41:45,060
And now you're kicking me out?

918
00:41:45,060 --> 00:41:46,770
Is that something
a decent person would do?

919
00:41:46,780 --> 00:41:47,820
I wouldn't dare.

920
00:41:47,820 --> 00:41:49,020
No, you would.

921
00:41:49,111 --> 00:41:50,822
What's wrong with sharing an apartment?

922
00:41:50,860 --> 00:41:53,270
It's normal for men and women
to share an apartment these days.

923
00:41:53,620 --> 00:41:55,740
Why are you so conservative
and old-fashioned?

924
00:41:56,060 --> 00:41:57,580
No. I just remember

925
00:41:58,020 --> 00:41:59,780
that we agreed before.

926
00:41:59,780 --> 00:42:02,980
Once your finances improved a little,

927
00:42:02,980 --> 00:42:03,820
you'd move out.

928
00:42:05,260 --> 00:42:06,460
If you'd just cut back a bit,

929
00:42:06,460 --> 00:42:09,020
you'd have enough money
to rent a place like mine.

930
00:42:09,220 --> 00:42:10,820
Why insist on living with me?

931
00:42:11,820 --> 00:42:12,900
Nothing's wrong.

932
00:42:13,220 --> 00:42:15,340
Once my finances improve, I'll move out.

933
00:42:16,500 --> 00:42:18,300
Let me show you my finances.

934
00:42:19,622 --> 00:42:21,570
This is all the money I have
across all my accounts.

935
00:42:21,580 --> 00:42:22,780
If there were money in them,

936
00:42:22,980 --> 00:42:24,020
I'd move out immediately.

937
00:42:24,020 --> 00:42:25,660
- I'm not looking. No.
- Check. Check it.

938
00:42:25,660 --> 00:42:26,340
Check it.

939
00:42:26,340 --> 00:42:27,700
I'm not checking it.

940
00:42:28,140 --> 00:42:29,980
Why would I check that? Take it away.

941
00:42:30,533 --> 00:42:31,422
Fine. Don't look.

942
00:42:32,220 --> 00:42:35,422
Your salary isn't exactly low.
But you're always throwing money around.

943
00:42:35,466 --> 00:42:36,622
Where does it all go?

944
00:42:40,380 --> 00:42:42,980
Forget it. To help you move out sooner,

945
00:42:43,488 --> 00:42:44,940
I'll teach you how to save money.

946
00:42:45,000 --> 00:42:46,380
You'll teach me how to save money?

947
00:42:46,460 --> 00:42:48,540
I'm all ears.
How exactly are you going to teach me?

948
00:42:50,420 --> 00:42:52,580
Saving money is my specialty.

949
00:42:56,420 --> 00:42:57,100
Excuse me.

950
00:42:57,288 --> 00:42:58,577
Could you pack this up for us?

951
00:42:58,860 --> 00:42:59,460
Thank you.

952
00:43:00,420 --> 00:43:01,900
How much can that possibly save?

953
00:43:03,180 --> 00:43:04,180
Two days' worth of meals.

954
00:43:05,060 --> 00:43:06,860
=Love Has Fireworks=
(Next Episode Preview)

955
00:43:08,020 --> 00:43:08,933
You two already knew

956
00:43:08,940 --> 00:43:10,940
that Wang Ruohai had gone to Shanlifang,
didn't you?

957
00:43:11,100 --> 00:43:13,090
Shanlifang is Xinxin Vision's
parent company.

958
00:43:13,260 --> 00:43:15,380
Wang Ruohai just became
their new Finance Director.

959
00:43:15,980 --> 00:43:17,540
Why didn't you tell me earlier?

960
00:43:18,460 --> 00:43:19,020
Ms. Fang,

961
00:43:19,511 --> 00:43:21,100
I've run into a bit of trouble lately.

962
00:43:23,340 --> 00:43:25,260
Is there anyone at Hejing

963
00:43:25,260 --> 00:43:26,340
you think

964
00:43:26,860 --> 00:43:27,940
could help you out?

965
00:43:28,020 --> 00:43:29,600
Someone like Qian Fei, for example.

966
00:43:29,620 --> 00:43:32,220
Would you mind letting her
work as my special assistant

967
00:43:32,220 --> 00:43:33,260
while we're collaborating?

968
00:43:33,980 --> 00:43:35,020
What do you think?

969
00:43:47,671 --> 00:43:52,031
♪There's no need
to know the ending from the start♪

970
00:43:54,371 --> 00:43:59,501
♪Let the melody play through the chords
with the wind♪

971
00:44:02,611 --> 00:44:06,821
♪There's no need
to keep every promise from the past♪

972
00:44:09,151 --> 00:44:15,141
♪Leave some surprises
for the unknown in life♪

973
00:44:17,281 --> 00:44:22,271
♪There's no need
to force things between two people♪

974
00:44:23,941 --> 00:44:29,761
♪Perhaps I'll feel alone,
yet still find you there for me♪

975
00:44:32,001 --> 00:44:37,711
♪There's no need
to dwell on right or wrong, nor fear♪

976
00:44:38,641 --> 00:44:45,271
♪A hug means more
than countless apologies♪

977
00:44:45,491 --> 00:44:48,621
♪I'll send you into the wide world♪

978
00:44:48,891 --> 00:44:52,771
♪To live with passion
and become who you truly are♪

979
00:44:53,441 --> 00:44:55,171
♪A quiet shoulder♪

980
00:44:55,171 --> 00:45:00,041
♪Like a harbor waiting
for your wandering soul♪

981
00:45:00,431 --> 00:45:03,411
♪I'll wait for the day
you return to a simpler life♪

982
00:45:03,641 --> 00:45:07,761
♪The lights of home warm the night♪

983
00:45:08,161 --> 00:45:10,251
♪A companionship that lasts forever♪

984
00:45:10,251 --> 00:45:14,161
♪Shining brightly
like the stars and the moon on high♪

985
00:45:14,901 --> 00:45:18,131
♪I'll send you into the wide world♪

986
00:45:18,411 --> 00:45:22,641
♪To live with passion
and become who you truly are♪

987
00:45:23,011 --> 00:45:24,731
♪A quiet shoulder♪

988
00:45:24,731 --> 00:45:29,391
♪Like a harbor waiting
for your wandering soul♪

989
00:45:29,931 --> 00:45:32,911
♪I'll wait for the day
you return to a simpler life♪

990
00:45:33,091 --> 00:45:37,411
♪The lights of home warm the night♪

991
00:45:37,711 --> 00:45:40,681
♪A companionship that lasts forever♪

992
00:45:41,541 --> 00:45:49,481
♪Shining brightly
like the stars and the moon on high♪

